        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 11:43AM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 1143 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Oak Grove, or 10 miles
west of Mountain Park, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Canton, Woodstock, Holly Springs, Buffington, Hickory Flat, Union
Hill, Kellogg Creek, Oak Grove, Little River Landing, Lebanon,
Hobgood Park, Bridgemill, and Sutallee.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
